{
  "stem": "6076.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So mostly, the butcher sold it to the Christians, which they did a good business, you know?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, we had very few Christian butchers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The only butchers the war, it was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Christians, they like to buy that part of the meat, which was very good meat-- the-- the lower part.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it turned out that a [NON-ENGLISH] was never rich.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He couldn't become rich.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he was a Talmudical scholar.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was a very-- he was very fine and educated man, which people in the city respect him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As, like, you know, different.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, he was very educated in his-- in his law.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Actually a [NON-ENGLISH] is like a veterinarian-- veterinarian's law, the same education.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, you have to study when an animal can live.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When the animal has no-- cannot live without disease, the animal is not kosher.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's very important.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So for my father to study before he became a [NON-ENGLISH], it's like you study like doctor, you know, to be a doctor in that profession.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Even a chicken-- sometimes, if you open a chicken in those years, sometimes we did see a nail going through the stomach.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't kosher.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The chicken could not live with a rusted nail going through, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So many times it was so difficult.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It wasn't so-- it was-- it was funny, but was not funny when many times a woman would come in with a chicken, you know, covered with a white tissue or towel.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she will say to my father please, Mr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Warszauer.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Would you-- you know, I have the chicken.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it's Friday late.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Would you tell me?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I found this and this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Would you tell me if the chicken is kosher?",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
